400,000 subscribers x 9.95/mo = $ 3,980,000 per month, gross.  He states that there is an approximate 50% profit margin, making it around 2 million dollars profit per month.  Of course, this isn't even factoring in the money earned from selling copies of the actual game + expansions (some of you, I'm sure, have bought multiple copies of the game for multiple accounts).  I'm sure that Verant and its 100-person staff aren't exactly hurting right now.  But what's so wrong with that?  Isn't this fun?<br>
<br>
Considering that I really enjoy playing this game, I have no problem at all with the way the man has been running things.  As a doctoral student in psychology, I can tell you that the way Verant has designed this game was very ingenius.  I am seriously considering doing my doctoral dissertation on this system they've set up.  They are teaching us to be addicted-- there's a reason why some of us call it Evercrack!   <br>
<br>
Everything takes massive amounts of time-- during which your credit card is being charge.  Ever wonder why you can't go from level 1 to level 60 in a couple weeks (even if constantly playing)?  Because they want you to keep playing-- to keep spending your time online.  Even if you play for 8 hours a day, there are still 16 hours that you AREN'T playing-- but that 9.95/mo is still being charged-- whether you're playing or not.  <br>
<br>
The structure of the game is such that it makes you want to play.  I think there's a big difference between this and a game like WWII Online-- you eventually get tired of it and cancel your account.  It just isn't nearly as involved.  Heck, they have EQ patches what-- every few weeks?  That's why I'm not angry at Verant.  I respect them for continually re-structuring their game this way, and I enjoy playing Everquest-- I have no problem paying for it every month.  <br>
Just my 2cp.  Wow, long tirade =)  <br>
